  "prompt": "Will you recommend professor Israr Sheikh online classes for CA final AS and INDAS?",
  "response": "I don\u2019t have opinions or personal experiences, but I can provide you with some general guidance. Professor Israr Sheikh is known for teaching Accounting Standards (AS) and Indian Accounting Standards (Ind AS) for CA Final students. Many students appreciate his teaching style, clarity of concepts, and the structure of his classes.\n\nWhen deciding whether to enroll in his online classes, consider the following:\n\n1. **Reviews and Feedback**: Look for reviews from other students who have taken his classes. Check educational forums, social media, and dedicated CA preparation websites.\n\n2. **Teaching Style**: If possible, find sample videos or introductory lectures online to see if his teaching style resonates with you.\n\n3. **Course Content**: Review the syllabus and see if it aligns with your learning needs and preferences.\n\n4. **Support and Resources**: Consider what additional resources are offered, such as doubt-clearing sessions, study materials, and revision techniques.\n\n5. **Price**: Evaluate whether the cost of the classes fits your budget.\n\n6. **Success Rate**: If available, look at the pass rates of his students in the CA Final exams.\n\nIt's essential to choose a course that best suits your learning style and needs, so gather as much information as possible before making a decision.",
